I went through the homepage at desktop, tablet, and mobile widths. There are a lot of issues that work against a premium feel — most of them are layout/overflow problems and rough responsive breakpoints. Here's what I found, grouped by severity.

**Critical layout problems (visible at desktop ~1127px)**

The biggest issue is that the entire page appears to be rendered inside a fixed-width container (looks like ~1127–1200px) with no responsive scaling. At any viewport narrower than that, the content gets clipped on the right side. You can see this clearly in several places: the hero headline "TO GLOBAL MARKETS" runs off the right edge, the "Get a Quote" button in the header is half-cut, the products row (Teja, Byadgi, Turmeric, Coffee, Spice Powders) bleeds off-screen, and the gallery grid shows partial tiles on the right. There's also a visible vertical scroll-bar artifact (a thin red/orange bar) hugging the right edge in multiple sections, which suggests a custom scroll indicator that isn't accounting for viewport width.

**Section overlap / vertical spacing**

Several sections collide into each other instead of having clean separation. The "Our Origin" section ends and the cream/beige image block visibly overlaps the dark "Our Products" section below it (the "OUR PRODUCTS" label appears on top of the lighter panel). Similarly, the stats row (Countries Exported / Tons Delivered / Global Partners / Years Experience) overlaps the product cards above it and the "Our Process" heading below it. The Certifications cards (ISO 22000, HACCP, APEDA) collide with the "Global Reach" section text and with the "GALLERY" heading. These look like negative margins or absolute-positioned elements that weren't accounted for.

**The "Our Origin" / world map section**

The big right-side area next to "Rooted in Guntur, Trusted Worldwide" is completely empty at this width — you can faintly see the world map appear later, but the cities (Dubai, London, New York, etc.) and the "Exporting to 20+ Countries Across 4 Continents" callout are missing entirely. The map itself only shows a faint arc with "Guntur, India" — the rest of the cities/animation isn't visible. This is a flagship section and it currently reads as broken.

**Animated counters stuck at zero**

The stats display "0+ COUNTRIES EXPORTED", "0+ TONS DELIVERED", "0+ GLOBAL PARTNERS", "0+ YEARS EXPERIENCE" on initial render and only count up partway as you scroll (I saw 2+, 142+, 7+ frozen mid-animation in one frame, and 4+, 231+, 11+, 3+ in another). The numbers don't seem to settle at the final intended values consistently — "231+ tons delivered" looks like a partial animation state, not a real number. Either the IntersectionObserver isn't firing reliably or the animation doesn't complete.

**Typography / hierarchy**

The serif display font is nice, but the hero ("TO GLOBAL MARKETS") is so large it can't fit one line at this viewport, and there's no fluid `clamp()` sizing to scale it down. The section headings ("Rooted in Guntur, Trusted Worldwide", "From Farm to World With Care", "Fields, Facilities & Beyond", "Let's Grow Together") are also fixed-size and don't scale. The body copy in the "Our Origin" panel has extremely low contrast (very light gray-tan on cream) and is hard to read. The eyebrow labels ("OUR ORIGIN", "OUR PRODUCTS", etc.) sit too close to their headings with no breathing room.

**Navigation**

The hamburger menu kicks in too early — it appears around 895px, which is well into tablet/laptop territory. A premium site should keep the full nav until ~1024px or lower. On mobile (390px) the initial hero state shows no logo and no hamburger at all until you scroll a little, which is jarring. The "Get a Quote" CTA in the header is rendered as a thin pill outline that gets clipped at narrower widths.

**Mobile (390px) specific**

The hamburger appears, but the hero text "FROM THE FIELDS OF INDIA / TO GLOBAL MARKETS" is entirely missing from the first viewport — only the image is shown. The stats section continues to overlap the "Our Process" heading. The "Discover Our Origin" link and the image below it are crammed together with no spacing. The product cards stack acceptably but the section padding is inconsistent.

**Visual polish issues that hurt premium feel**

The "Watch Our Story" play button is a thin circle outline that looks underpowered next to the bold "Explore Our Products →" pill — they're styled like two different design systems. The "01 — 05" scroll counter and vertical "SCROLL ↓" label in the hero are good ideas but feel disconnected (one bottom-left, one bottom-right, different sizing). The footer is dense and cramped, with the logo "DECCAN HARVESTS" splitting across two lines awkwardly. The "Let's Grow Together" red section is a striking color choice but the contrast between the red background and the gold "SEND REQUEST" button is muddy; the form inputs are nearly invisible (transparent on red with thin underlines).

**Smaller things worth fixing**

The "N" floating circle in the bottom-left is unexplained — looks like a stray dev/preview indicator. The gallery tiles have inconsistent aspect ratios and the bottom-right tile shows a dark-on-dark image that reads as a broken/empty thumbnail. The "+ 8 MORE" pill at the end of the country list is styled differently from the other country labels. The Cheese image in the gallery seems off-brand for a spice company.

**Recommended priority order**

The first thing to fix is the container width / overflow problem — set the layout to be fluid (max-width with proper responsive padding) so nothing gets clipped at common laptop widths like 1280, 1366, and 1440. After that, audit every section for negative margins or absolute positioning causing the overlaps. Then fix the counter animation, the missing world-map content, and the navigation breakpoint. Typography scaling with `clamp()` and tightening the form/CTA styling in the red section will get you most of the way to a polished premium look.

I dug into the live DOM and computed styles. Most of what looked like layout chaos is actually a small set of root-cause problems. Here's what's really happening and concrete code fixes for each.

## The single biggest fix: viewport-width root cause

Your `<body>` has `overflow-x: hidden` set globally (I confirmed it: `bodyOverflow: "hidden"`). That's masking real layout overflow rather than fixing it. Worse, you have a `.grain` overlay div that's **1782px wide** sitting inside a 891px body — which would normally cause horizontal scroll but is being hidden by the body rule. The first reflex is to keep `overflow-x: hidden`, but that hides the symptoms while the underlying overflow keeps clipping content.

Fix the grain overlay so it doesn't overflow:

```css
.grain {
  position: fixed;        /* if it isn't already */
  inset: 0;
  width: 100%;            /* not a hardcoded pixel size */
  height: 100%;
  pointer-events: none;
  /* if you used background-size for a texture, keep that */
}
```

Then remove the body-level `overflow-x: hidden` and add it only on the specific sections that legitimately need it (your hero already has `overflow-hidden`, which is fine for the video bleed):

```css
/* globals.css */
html, body { overflow-x: clip; }   /* `clip` instead of `hidden` — doesn't create a scroll container, prevents accidental scroll-anchoring issues with Lenis */
```

The reason this matters: you're using Lenis smooth scrolling (I saw `class="lenis"` on `<html>`). Lenis + `overflow: hidden` on body creates scroll-jank and is one reason your scroll-triggered counters and reveal animations stall mid-animation.

## Hero — fix the offscreen headline

Your hero already uses `clamp(4rem, 10vw, 9rem)` which is good, but the words are wrapped in three separate `<div class="overflow-hidden">` wrappers (for the line-reveal animation) inside a `flex-wrap` container. At ~1127px viewport, `10vw ≈ 113px` per character — "MARKETS" alone is 800px+ and won't fit next to "GLOBAL" on one line, so it wraps and the second line gets clipped by `h-screen min-h-[600px]`.

