## Stats section — counters stuck at 0

I confirmed in the DOM that all four `<span>` values literally contain `"0+"` as static text. There's a Framer Motion / IntersectionObserver counter component that should be replacing this text but isn't firing (or fires once for the wrong target). The reason this stalls is almost certainly Lenis again: Lenis transforms the document, which can confuse IntersectionObserver with default `rootMargin`. Two fixes:

```tsx
// CounterUp.tsx
import { useInView, useMotionValue, useTransform, animate } from 'framer-motion';

export function CounterUp({ to, duration = 2.2 }: { to: number; duration?: number }) {
  const ref = useRef<HTMLSpanElement>(null);
  const inView = useInView(ref, { once: true, margin: '0px 0px -20% 0px' });
  const mv = useMotionValue(0);
  const rounded = useTransform(mv, v => `${Math.round(v)}+`);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!inView) return;
    const controls = animate(mv, to, { duration, ease: [0.16, 1, 0.3, 1] });
    return controls.stop;
  }, [inView, to]);

  return <motion.span ref={ref}>{rounded}</motion.span>;
}
```

And in the parent stats grid:

```tsx
<CounterUp to={42} />   {/* not 0 — the real target */}
<CounterUp to={3500} />
<CounterUp to={180} />
<CounterUp to={15} />
```

The "142+" and "231+" frames I caught earlier are clearly mid-animation states the page was rendering when I screenshotted — they're not the final number, they're whatever Framer Motion happened to be at the moment IntersectionObserver triggered (sometimes from above, sometimes from below, depending on Lenis scroll position). Adding `once: true` and a generous bottom `margin` fixes it.

