# Order to apply

Apply in this order — each step's effect will be visible before you start the next:

The `globals.css` patch is step one and removes the largest class of visual bugs by itself (the grain overflow, the missing input styles, the motion fallbacks). Then the Hero changes restore the headline at all viewports. Then the Origin section's `max-w-2xl` + the `data-city` attribute restores the world map. Then the `CounterUp` component fixes the stuck zeros. Then the Certifications/GlobalReach split fixes the overlap. Then the Products/Gallery breakpoint changes clean up the right-edge clipping. Header polish, Contact form container, and Footer logo are last — they're all aesthetic improvements that only matter once the layout is correct.

